1
00:00:03,254 --> 00:00:05,507
<i>Within the spreading darkness</i>

2
00:00:05,590 --> 00:00:08,259
<i>I pledged a vow to the revolution</i>

3
00:00:08,343 --> 00:00:13,264
<i>I can't let anybody interrupt it</i>

4
00:00:13,348 --> 00:00:18,436
<i>I'm going to change</i>

5
00:00:26,861 --> 00:00:31,115
<i>The future that
the forbidden fruit foretells...</i>

6
00:00:31,366 --> 00:00:35,245
<i>I'm going to change</i>

7
00:00:35,328 --> 00:00:39,582
<i>The dream into reality</i>

8
00:00:42,377 --> 00:00:48,341
<i>The ending</i>

9
00:00:48,424 --> 00:00:51,469
<i>That everybody wants</i>

10
00:00:52,428 --> 00:00:54,722
<i>Within the spreading darkness</i>

11
00:00:54,806 --> 00:00:57,475
<i>I pledged our vow to the revolution</i>

12
00:00:57,559 --> 00:01:02,355
<i>I can't let anybody interrupt it</i>

13
00:01:02,522 --> 00:01:07,735
<i>Someday I'll show you</i>

14
00:01:07,819 --> 00:01:11,489
<i>A bright and ideal</i>

15
00:01:11,573 --> 00:01:17,161
<i>World</i>

16
00:01:25,962 --> 00:01:29,007
EXECUTION

17
00:01:32,677 --> 00:01:36,431
Use it just like that to kill
the criminals who are broadcast.

18
00:01:37,098 --> 00:01:40,101
Then, you can use the notebook
however you want.

19
00:01:40,226 --> 00:01:41,644
Those are the conditions.

20
00:01:42,854 --> 00:01:45,023
<i>If everything goes according to
Light Yagami's plans,</i>

21
00:01:45,231 --> 00:01:47,025
<i>this is sure to save Misa...</i>

22
00:01:48,526 --> 00:01:52,822
This is a good deal
for both of us, isn't it?

23
00:01:53,323 --> 00:01:57,035
Or I guess as you would say...
it's good business.

24
00:02:02,790 --> 00:02:05,460
FIFTIETH DAY

25
00:02:06,336 --> 00:02:09,005
There's no reason for you
to stay there like that.

26
00:02:09,839 --> 00:02:14,969
<i>It's been over a month since Kira
started to kill criminals again...</i>

27
00:02:15,470 --> 00:02:18,640
<i>I am sure that my son isn't Kira...</i>

28
00:02:19,223 --> 00:02:23,019
<i>Now, all that's left
is for you to be sure...</i>

29
00:02:23,561 --> 00:02:27,273
<i>I get out when my son does...</i>

30
00:02:29,192 --> 00:02:30,777
The Chief sure is stubborn...

31
00:02:32,528 --> 00:02:34,197
Light, are you all right?

32
00:02:35,031 --> 00:02:38,534
<i>Yeah. I'm all right, but...Ryuzaki...</i>

33
00:02:38,868 --> 00:02:42,163
<i>criminals have stopped dying
since I've been confined.</i>

34
00:02:42,830 --> 00:02:45,291
<i>I think it's highly likely that
Kira is someone</i>

35
00:02:45,375 --> 00:02:47,919
<i>who knows about my situation.</i>

36
00:02:48,169 --> 00:02:49,295
<i>- If we go with this line of reasoning. ..
- No.</i>

37
00:02:49,379 --> 00:02:52,632
Criminals are not dying
because you are Kira.

38
00:02:52,840 --> 00:02:54,801
<i>No! I'm not Kira.</i>

39
00:02:54,884 --> 00:02:56,219
<i>How many times must
I say it until you'll understand?</i>

40
00:02:57,679 --> 00:03:01,265
<i>Kira should know that killings
have begun again...</i>

41
00:03:02,058 --> 00:03:03,142
<i>It doesn't seem like he knows...</i>

42
00:03:04,143 --> 00:03:05,520
This is cruel, Ryuzaki...

43
00:03:06,062 --> 00:03:09,565
You still haven't told Light that
criminals are being killed again...

44
00:03:11,567 --> 00:03:12,652
<i>Amane...</i>

45
00:03:12,735 --> 00:03:13,778
Yes?

46
00:03:13,861 --> 00:03:15,780
<i>I know you're tired,
but are you all right?</i>

47
00:03:16,781 --> 00:03:18,241
Are you stupid?

48
00:03:18,783 --> 00:03:20,493
There'd be something
wrong with me

49
00:03:20,576 --> 00:03:22,203
if I was all right after
all these days...

50
00:03:23,079 --> 00:03:24,163
<i>Yes, that's true.</i>

51
00:03:25,206 --> 00:03:28,710
Let me go...
I want to see Light...

52
00:03:29,502 --> 00:03:30,628
Light...

53
00:03:31,254 --> 00:03:32,380
Light...

54
00:03:33,089 --> 00:03:34,132
<i>Light...</i>

55
00:03:35,800 --> 00:03:38,636
it seems like all three
of them are at their limit...

56
00:03:38,928 --> 00:03:41,764
Ryuzaki, why are you
still detaining Light?

57
00:03:42,098 --> 00:03:43,266
You should let him go already!

58
00:03:43,433 --> 00:03:45,184
If you do, the Chief
will come out too.

59
00:03:45,810 --> 00:03:47,353
Criminals are still being killed

60
00:03:47,437 --> 00:03:50,064
even though Misa and Light aren't
able to obtain any information.

61
00:03:50,523 --> 00:03:52,608
We know at least that much.

62
00:03:53,443 --> 00:03:54,485
No.

63
00:03:54,736 --> 00:03:58,823
All we know is that Amane harbors an
unnaturally strong love for Light Yagami.

64
00:04:00,074 --> 00:04:03,661
Ryuzaki. .. Sorry, but I think
that you're doing this

65
00:04:03,745 --> 00:04:07,999
because you don't want to admit
that you were wrong about Light.

66
00:04:08,541 --> 00:04:09,834
I figured you might think that.

67
00:04:11,210 --> 00:04:15,298
As Light has said, Kira's killed
Lind L.Tailor and the FBI agents.

68
00:04:15,965 --> 00:04:18,217
If Kira could kill under surveillance and
without obtaining information,

69
00:04:18,301 --> 00:04:21,012
there would have been no need
to kill Tailor and the FBI agents!

70
00:04:21,137 --> 00:04:23,973
No matter how hard we investigate,
he can't be traced.

71
00:04:24,557 --> 00:04:26,142
Kira doesn't kill without a reason.

72
00:04:26,684 --> 00:04:28,811
You even said so yourself.

73
00:04:29,645 --> 00:04:30,730
I see...

74
00:04:31,022 --> 00:04:32,857
If he could kill
in these circumstances,

75
00:04:32,940 --> 00:04:36,277
he shouldn't have had a problem
with leaving those FBI agents alone...

76
00:04:38,321 --> 00:04:39,739
It's already been fifty days...

77
00:04:40,364 --> 00:04:42,116
There's no reason to be doing this.

78
00:04:42,992 --> 00:04:46,078
Besides that, we should be thinking
of ways to catch the real Kira.

79
00:05:03,054 --> 00:05:04,180
I understand.

80
00:05:06,891 --> 00:05:07,892
<i>Mr. Yagami.</i>

81
00:05:08,392 --> 00:05:09,393
What is it?

82
00:05:09,727 --> 00:05:12,021
<i>Will you return to
task force headquarters?</i>

83
00:05:12,772 --> 00:05:15,650
<i>I want you to hear my theory
on what's happening.</i>

84
00:05:16,734 --> 00:05:19,862
<i>But first, I want to talk to you
as Light's father.</i>

85
00:05:21,823 --> 00:05:22,865
All right.

86
00:05:41,175 --> 00:05:45,137
THREE DAYS LATER

87
00:05:46,138 --> 00:05:49,642
I never thought that you would
be an old man, Mister Stalker.

88
00:05:49,934 --> 00:05:52,395
I'm not a stalker. I'm a detective.

89
00:05:52,979 --> 00:05:53,980
<i>A detective?!</i>

90
00:05:54,522 --> 00:05:55,690
I remember now!

91
00:05:56,148 --> 00:05:59,277
I was told that I was being arrested
for being the Second Kira or something...

92
00:05:59,360 --> 00:06:01,153
That was for real?

93
00:06:01,946 --> 00:06:02,989
No way...

94
00:06:03,072 --> 00:06:06,576
The police wouldn't
tie me up like that...

95
00:06:07,118 --> 00:06:09,078
Anyways, it's kind of funny how

96
00:06:09,161 --> 00:06:11,747
my hands and feet are restrained
even though you're going to let me go?

97
00:06:12,373 --> 00:06:13,457
Be quiet.

98
00:06:26,095 --> 00:06:27,805
- Light!
- Misa?

99
00:06:27,930 --> 00:06:29,473
I was dying to see you!

100
00:06:29,765 --> 00:06:31,434
Dad, what's going on?

101
00:06:31,934 --> 00:06:33,519
Huh? Dad?
Oh no!

102
00:06:33,769 --> 00:06:36,772
I called your dad a stalker and
other rude things like that...

103
00:06:36,981 --> 00:06:37,982
Pleased to meet you.

104
00:06:38,065 --> 00:06:39,901
My name is Misa Amane.
I'm currently going outwith Light-!

105
00:06:39,984 --> 00:06:41,444
I leave it to you, Chief.

106
00:06:44,780 --> 00:06:46,574
What's wrong?
Hurry up and get in.

107
00:06:52,622 --> 00:06:56,208
We're finally cleared
and are free to go, right?

108
00:06:56,876 --> 00:06:57,960
No...

109
00:06:58,502 --> 00:07:01,881
You two are now...
being taken to your execution.

110
00:07:03,883 --> 00:07:07,386
An execution ground has been prepared
in an underground facility.

111
00:07:07,553 --> 00:07:10,056
I volunteered to escort you there.

112
00:07:10,306 --> 00:07:11,557
- Our execution?
- What?!

113
00:07:11,641 --> 00:07:13,559
- What are you talking about, Dad?
- This is a joke, isn't it?

114
00:07:13,643 --> 00:07:15,645
I has decided that
Light Yagami is Kira

115
00:07:15,728 --> 00:07:18,272
and Misa Amane is
the Second Kira.

116
00:07:18,481 --> 00:07:22,985
L's declared that if you were executed,
the killings would stop.

117
00:07:23,653 --> 00:07:25,821
Haven't the killings stopped?

118
00:07:26,072 --> 00:07:27,823
No, they're still continuing.

119
00:07:27,990 --> 00:07:31,535
Continuing?
That's not what he told me...

120
00:07:32,244 --> 00:07:35,623
I was trying to get
a confession out of you.

121
00:07:36,040 --> 00:07:37,708
That's not the problem here.

122
00:07:38,584 --> 00:07:43,839
L's suggestion that the killings
would stop if you two were eliminated...

123
00:07:44,048 --> 00:07:46,842
was immediately accepted
by all the top officials of the UN

124
00:07:46,926 --> 00:07:48,135
and the Japanese government.

125
00:07:48,636 --> 00:07:51,973
Kira will be eradicated in secret.

126
00:07:52,348 --> 00:07:55,434
That's crazy.
Wait, Dad, I'm not Kira!

127
00:07:55,518 --> 00:07:57,770
That's right, sir.
What are you thinking?!

128
00:07:57,853 --> 00:07:59,230
He's your own son!

129
00:07:59,397 --> 00:08:03,025
This is not my decision, it's L's.

130
00:08:04,026 --> 00:08:08,614
He has solved many difficult cases
in the past and never been wrong.

131
00:08:09,865 --> 00:08:13,160
Dad...
Do you believe L over me?

132
00:08:14,161 --> 00:08:16,872
I says that if the killings don't stop,

133
00:08:16,998 --> 00:08:19,917
then he'll take responsibility
and end his own life...

134
00:08:21,502 --> 00:08:23,546
L... What are you thinking?

135
00:08:24,005 --> 00:08:26,048
I understand that from the facts
that we have up to now,

136
00:08:26,132 --> 00:08:28,384
this may seem like
the only logical assumption...

137
00:08:29,010 --> 00:08:30,428
But this is wrong!

138
00:08:31,053 --> 00:08:33,014
Why did L come to this conclusion?

139
00:08:34,015 --> 00:08:35,182
Something's strange...

140
00:08:35,266 --> 00:08:37,351
This isn't like L at all...

141
00:08:37,935 --> 00:08:41,856
L's always used hard evidence
in all of his cases.

142
00:08:42,273 --> 00:08:43,983
Why would he let
this one end like this?

143
00:08:44,734 --> 00:08:46,110
We're almost there.

144
00:09:04,170 --> 00:09:05,337
Where are we?

145
00:09:05,880 --> 00:09:07,631
Why did you bring us out to
the middle of nowhere?

146
00:09:08,049 --> 00:09:09,091
What are you going to do?

147
00:09:09,675 --> 00:09:11,844
Are you going to let us go?

148
00:09:12,762 --> 00:09:15,931
Nobody will see us here...

149
00:09:16,432 --> 00:09:20,311
I decided to bring you here
instead of the execution ground.

150
00:09:22,229 --> 00:09:23,230
Light...

151
00:09:25,107 --> 00:09:27,693
I'm going to kill you here
and then kill myself.

152
00:09:29,111 --> 00:09:30,404
What are you talking about, Dad!

153
00:09:30,488 --> 00:09:32,198
- That's crazy!
- Stop it already! You're crazy!

154
00:09:32,782 --> 00:09:34,617
You're going to kill your child
and kill yourself?

155
00:09:34,742 --> 00:09:37,078
If you want to die, then why don't
you just die by yourself!

156
00:09:37,161 --> 00:09:39,121
If you do this, then you'll be
no different from Kira.

157
00:09:39,330 --> 00:09:40,956
No... I'm different from Kira.

158
00:09:41,248 --> 00:09:45,628
I have a responsibility as a parent
and as the Detective Superintendent!

159
00:09:45,961 --> 00:09:47,797
Dad, Misa's right!

160
00:09:48,130 --> 00:09:50,800
If we die here,
we'll never uncover the truth!

161
00:09:51,008 --> 00:09:52,218
It would be better if we ran away!

162
00:09:52,301 --> 00:09:53,427
It's too late, Light...

163
00:09:54,678 --> 00:09:56,472
Either way, you'll be executed...

164
00:09:57,098 --> 00:09:59,308
At least this way. . .it'll be...
by my own hand.

165
00:10:01,936 --> 00:10:04,105
Stop, Dad! I'm not Kira!

166
00:10:04,396 --> 00:10:06,148
If I die here,
we all fall into Kira's trap!

167
00:10:06,315 --> 00:10:07,566
Don't you see?!

168
00:10:09,026 --> 00:10:11,987
Amane. .. I'm going to die here
with my son.

169
00:10:12,530 --> 00:10:14,532
I have no reason to kill you.

170
00:10:15,449 --> 00:10:18,035
The police will probably
find this car soon.

171
00:10:18,744 --> 00:10:21,789
You'll be executed
at the planned site.

172
00:10:25,251 --> 00:10:30,381
Light...from one murderer to another,
I'll see you in hell!

173
00:10:31,632 --> 00:10:32,758
Dad!

174
00:10:35,886 --> 00:10:37,680
Stop!

175
00:10:51,735 --> 00:10:55,698
Light...from one murderer to another,
I'll see you in hell.

176
00:10:55,781 --> 00:10:56,866
Dad!

177
00:11:16,927 --> 00:11:18,220
A blank?

178
00:11:21,849 --> 00:11:23,142
Thank goodness...

179
00:11:23,934 --> 00:11:27,229
"Thank goodness?"
What are you doing, Dad?

180
00:11:27,897 --> 00:11:29,356
Forgive me, you two...

181
00:11:30,191 --> 00:11:34,028
This was the only way to
free you from confinement...

182
00:11:34,695 --> 00:11:35,988
But please understand...

183
00:11:36,572 --> 00:11:40,075
I did this because I believe
that you're not Kira...

184
00:11:41,076 --> 00:11:42,411
Were you watching, Ryuzaki?

185
00:11:42,870 --> 00:11:44,371
I did as you said,

186
00:11:44,538 --> 00:11:46,207
and as you can see,
I'm still alive.

187
00:11:47,917 --> 00:11:50,127
<i>Yes, it was a convincing performance.</i>

188
00:11:51,212 --> 00:11:53,214
If Amane were the Second Kira,

189
00:11:53,297 --> 00:11:55,549
who can kill just by
knowing a person's face,

190
00:11:55,758 --> 00:11:59,511
then she would have killed you
before you fired.

191
00:12:00,346 --> 00:12:02,514
Also, if Light were Kira,

192
00:12:02,723 --> 00:12:06,435
the Kira I know would even kill
his parents if he was in trouble.

193
00:12:07,186 --> 00:12:09,980
In Light's case, I cannot deny
the possibility

194
00:12:10,064 --> 00:12:12,107
that he may have discovered
it was all an act halfway through.

195
00:12:12,566 --> 00:12:16,153
But as I promised,
I will end their confinement.

196
00:12:17,071 --> 00:12:18,864
Also as promised,

197
00:12:18,948 --> 00:12:21,784
even though she insists that
those tapes were just occult videos,

198
00:12:22,117 --> 00:12:23,202
we have various pieces of evidence

199
00:12:23,285 --> 00:12:25,246
and a confession that
she sent the Kira videos.

200
00:12:25,621 --> 00:12:26,997
So Misa Amane will remain
under surveillance

201
00:12:27,081 --> 00:12:29,541
until Kira is caught and
his case is resolved.

202
00:12:29,750 --> 00:12:31,669
<i>What's with that?
Do you still suspect me?</i>

203
00:12:32,544 --> 00:12:36,090
Well, you get to return to
your normal life.

204
00:12:36,799 --> 00:12:38,175
If you're not guilty,

205
00:12:38,259 --> 00:12:41,387
you can think of the surveillance
as police protection.

206
00:12:42,429 --> 00:12:45,557
I see. Since I'm not the Second Kira,

207
00:12:45,641 --> 00:12:48,060
I should think of it like
I have some bodyguards.

208
00:12:48,644 --> 00:12:50,938
<i>Also Light...</i>

209
00:12:51,438 --> 00:12:54,775
I will make arrangements so that you
and I will be together 24 hours a day,

210
00:12:54,858 --> 00:12:57,319
working on the investigation.

211
00:13:04,493 --> 00:13:08,372
All right, Ryuzaki.
Let's catch Kira together.

212
00:13:08,872 --> 00:13:10,958
<i>Yes. I'm looking forward
to working with you.</i>

213
00:13:16,213 --> 00:13:18,382
Is this really necessary, Ryuzaki?

214
00:13:19,049 --> 00:13:21,510
I'm not doing this
because I want to.

215
00:13:21,802 --> 00:13:25,306
Huh? Is this what you meant by being
together with him 24 hours a day?

216
00:13:26,056 --> 00:13:27,850
Two guys chained together
is kinda gross...

217
00:13:27,933 --> 00:13:29,476
Ryuzaki, is that what you're into?

218
00:13:29,643 --> 00:13:32,563
I told you I'm not doing
this because I want to.

219
00:13:32,896 --> 00:13:35,232
But, Light belongs to Misa...

220
00:13:35,316 --> 00:13:37,067
If you're together with him
24 hours a day,

221
00:13:37,151 --> 00:13:38,944
then when will I have the time
to go on dates with him?

222
00:13:39,153 --> 00:13:42,114
Dates will be with the three of us.

223
00:13:42,531 --> 00:13:45,492
Huh? Are you telling me
we have to kiss in front of you?

224
00:13:45,826 --> 00:13:49,413
I'm not telling you to do anything.
But I will be watching.

225
00:13:49,621 --> 00:13:51,040
What's with that?

226
00:13:51,123 --> 00:13:52,583
You really are a pervert, aren't you?

227
00:13:52,666 --> 00:13:55,127
Light, please silence Misa.

228
00:13:55,753 --> 00:13:57,504
Misa, don't be selfish.

229
00:13:57,921 --> 00:14:00,924
You were definitely
the one who sent the tapes,

230
00:14:01,175 --> 00:14:04,386
just be grateful that you're allowed
as much freedom as this.

231
00:14:04,511 --> 00:14:06,597
Huh? What are you talking about?

232
00:14:06,680 --> 00:14:09,850
I'm your girlfriend, aren't I?
Don't you trust your own lover?

233
00:14:10,017 --> 00:14:13,604
Girlfriend? You said you fell in love
with me at first sight...

234
00:14:13,687 --> 00:14:15,647
It's one-sided and
you won't leave me alone.

235
00:14:16,273 --> 00:14:20,361
So then, you took advantage
of that fact and kissed me?

236
00:14:20,444 --> 00:14:23,238
Stupid! Stupid! Stupid! Stupid!

237
00:14:23,864 --> 00:14:25,449
About this "love at first sight" thing...

238
00:14:26,116 --> 00:14:29,078
It happened in Aoyama
on May 22, didn't it, Misa?

239
00:14:29,370 --> 00:14:30,371
Yes.

240
00:14:30,913 --> 00:14:32,998
Why did you go to Aoyama
on that day?

241
00:14:33,332 --> 00:14:34,583
What did you wear?

242
00:14:35,167 --> 00:14:37,127
I told you, I just happened
to go there.

243
00:14:37,211 --> 00:14:38,337
How many times have I told you?

244
00:14:38,420 --> 00:14:41,965
I don't really remember how
I felt that day or what I wore!

245
00:14:42,383 --> 00:14:45,928
Is it so wrong for me to be
hanging out in Aoyama without a reason?

246
00:14:46,136 --> 00:14:48,597
So when you came back
from Aoyama,

247
00:14:48,680 --> 00:14:50,557
you were in love with Light and

248
00:14:50,641 --> 00:14:51,892
- knew his name.
- Yes.

249
00:14:51,975 --> 00:14:54,895
You don't even know
how you knew his name.

250
00:14:54,978 --> 00:14:56,230
Yes. That's right.

251
00:14:56,438 --> 00:14:59,274
Then, how would you feel
if Light was Kira?

252
00:14:59,400 --> 00:15:01,902
Huh? If Light was Kira?

253
00:15:02,194 --> 00:15:03,278
That's right.

254
00:15:05,656 --> 00:15:07,074
That would be wonderful!

255
00:15:07,157 --> 00:15:08,992
I've always been grateful to Kira

256
00:15:09,076 --> 00:15:12,454
for punishing the man
who murdered my parents.

257
00:15:12,579 --> 00:15:16,166
If Light were Kira,
I'd love him more...

258
00:15:16,542 --> 00:15:19,920
Even though I love him
so much already!

259
00:15:20,254 --> 00:15:21,713
We're talking about Kira, here.

260
00:15:21,922 --> 00:15:23,507
You'd love him even more?

261
00:15:23,590 --> 00:15:25,426
Don't you feel afraid at all?

262
00:15:25,801 --> 00:15:27,678
That's supposing if Light is Kira, right?

263
00:15:27,886 --> 00:15:29,430
He's not scary at all.

264
00:15:29,596 --> 00:15:31,306
I'm one of those people
who accept Kira.

265
00:15:31,432 --> 00:15:34,893
I'd think of ways I could help him.

266
00:15:37,104 --> 00:15:40,607
You'd probably get in his way
rather than help him...

267
00:15:41,733 --> 00:15:42,734
According to this,

268
00:15:42,818 --> 00:15:45,988
there's no mistake that
you are the Second Kira,

269
00:15:47,114 --> 00:15:50,451
but it's so clear-cut that
I don't want to believe it.

270
00:15:50,617 --> 00:15:54,621
Good. Don't believe it,
because I'm not Kira!

271
00:15:54,955 --> 00:15:57,666
Anyway, you'll remain
under surveillance.

272
00:15:58,125 --> 00:16:01,837
When you go out, contact us using
this room's extension.

273
00:16:02,629 --> 00:16:04,089
From now on for private
and work-related affairs,

274
00:16:04,173 --> 00:16:07,009
Mr. Matsuda will accompany you
as your manager, Matsui.

275
00:16:07,092 --> 00:16:08,635
I've already paid off your agency

276
00:16:08,760 --> 00:16:10,971
- to agree to this.
- Hey there, I'm Matsui.

277
00:16:11,138 --> 00:16:14,683
I haven't told the police,
so be sure not to give yourself away.

278
00:16:15,225 --> 00:16:17,853
This old man's gonna be my manager?
How awful...

279
00:16:17,936 --> 00:16:21,064
No way!
What's wrong with me, Misa-Misa?

280
00:16:24,067 --> 00:16:27,571
Cut it outwith all this dating,
kissing, and Misa-Misa talk!

281
00:16:27,988 --> 00:16:29,239
This is the <i>Kira</i> case! Understand?!

282
00:16:29,323 --> 00:16:30,824
Take it seriously!

283
00:16:32,075 --> 00:16:33,118
Sorry.

284
00:16:33,827 --> 00:16:37,372
No, I'm sorry.
I know we're taking it seriously, but...

285
00:16:38,749 --> 00:16:40,792
Amane, go to your room now.

286
00:16:40,876 --> 00:16:41,877
What?

287
00:16:42,836 --> 00:16:44,171
No questions, c'mon.

288
00:16:45,088 --> 00:16:47,466
Light! Let's go on a date,
even if it's the three of us!

289
00:16:50,344 --> 00:16:52,387
Light, are you serious about Amane?

290
00:16:52,721 --> 00:16:55,849
No... As I said earlier,
it's one-sided...

291
00:16:55,933 --> 00:16:59,561
Then could you act as
if you're serious?

292
00:17:00,354 --> 00:17:02,272
I'm sure that Amane's connected
with the Second Kira

293
00:17:02,356 --> 00:17:03,774
from the video incident.

294
00:17:04,316 --> 00:17:07,027
And also from the way she loves you...

295
00:17:07,694 --> 00:17:09,279
Are you asking me to become
intimate with her

296
00:17:09,363 --> 00:17:11,573
so I can find out information
about the Second Kira?

297
00:17:12,199 --> 00:17:15,035
Yes. I think you can do it.

298
00:17:15,369 --> 00:17:18,455
And we could get the clues to solve
this case from Amane.

299
00:17:18,872 --> 00:17:21,124
This is why I released both of you.

300
00:17:23,043 --> 00:17:24,086
Ryuzaki...

301
00:17:25,420 --> 00:17:27,714
Even if it's for the Kira case,

302
00:17:27,881 --> 00:17:31,051
I could never toy with
a woman's emotions like that.

303
00:17:33,637 --> 00:17:35,013
I'm sorry,
you need to understand.

304
00:17:35,556 --> 00:17:39,476
To me, taking advantage of another
person's feelings is unforgivable,

305
00:17:39,560 --> 00:17:41,228
and the most despicable thing
a person can do.

306
00:17:42,229 --> 00:17:43,689
<i>There's something wrong...</i>

307
00:17:44,106 --> 00:17:46,066
<i>I can only assume that
his personality has changed...</i>

308
00:17:46,567 --> 00:17:48,277
<i>Is this really an act?</i>

309
00:17:49,152 --> 00:17:53,407
<i>At this rate, it sounds like Amane
was being controlled by Kira, but...</i>

310
00:17:54,575 --> 00:17:56,201
<i>Light Yagami as well...</i>

311
00:17:58,078 --> 00:17:59,246
What's wrong, Ryuzaki?

312
00:17:59,329 --> 00:18:01,248
Nothing. You're right.

313
00:18:02,082 --> 00:18:03,709
But, it would be helpful if
you could make sure

314
00:18:03,792 --> 00:18:08,130
she doesn't leak any information
about the investigation.

315
00:18:09,256 --> 00:18:15,262
Ryuzaki, can't we change this system
of changing hotels every few days?

316
00:18:15,929 --> 00:18:19,141
Yes. I've also been thinking about that.

317
00:18:19,641 --> 00:18:22,477
That's why. . .construction
started on this immediately after

318
00:18:22,561 --> 00:18:24,730
my first meeting with Mr. Yagami
and the others,

319
00:18:24,813 --> 00:18:26,773
when we decided
to investigate together.

320
00:18:27,399 --> 00:18:29,192
It will be completed in
just a few more days.

321
00:18:30,402 --> 00:18:31,486
This is it.

322
00:18:33,280 --> 00:18:35,782
It has twenty-three floors
above the ground and two below.

323
00:18:36,283 --> 00:18:38,702
It's built so you can't see it
from the outside,

324
00:18:38,785 --> 00:18:41,038
but there are two helicopters
on the roof.

325
00:18:41,121 --> 00:18:42,122
What?!

326
00:18:42,205 --> 00:18:43,206
That's amazing...

327
00:18:43,498 --> 00:18:46,585
I would like all of you to spend
as much time here as possible.

328
00:18:47,502 --> 00:18:49,087
Even if the number of investigators
increases on this case,

329
00:18:49,171 --> 00:18:51,256
we can accommodate
about sixty people.

330
00:18:52,215 --> 00:18:54,926
Misa will get her own floor
so that should keep her happy.

331
00:18:55,844 --> 00:18:59,014
This is really amazing...
but to go to these lengths...

332
00:18:59,306 --> 00:19:02,643
By the way, Ryuzaki, where's the money
to pay for this coming from?

333
00:19:03,226 --> 00:19:04,853
As you can see,

334
00:19:04,936 --> 00:19:07,481
I want to solve this case,
no matter what.

335
00:19:07,773 --> 00:19:08,815
That's what it means.

336
00:19:09,274 --> 00:19:10,984
No, you didn't answer the question.

337
00:19:11,151 --> 00:19:12,319
Yeah, that's right.

338
00:19:12,986 --> 00:19:15,238
The mass murders are bad enough,

339
00:19:15,572 --> 00:19:18,617
but I can't forgive the one who
put my dad and me through all of this.

340
00:19:19,493 --> 00:19:21,536
I want to solve this,
no matter what.

341
00:19:22,287 --> 00:19:23,955
"No matter what"? Then how about

342
00:19:24,039 --> 00:19:26,083
getting closer to Misa
and get her to reveal...

343
00:19:26,166 --> 00:19:28,502
I can't do that.
That's against my code.

344
00:19:28,877 --> 00:19:31,296
I see... That's too bad.

345
00:19:33,590 --> 00:19:36,468
Sorry, I just feel very motivated.

346
00:19:37,052 --> 00:19:39,096
Ryuzaki, Chief Yagami, Light...

347
00:19:39,513 --> 00:19:41,682
Let's all try to catch Kira,
no matter what!

348
00:19:42,516 --> 00:19:45,477
Excuse me...
But you didn't include me...

349
00:19:56,446 --> 00:20:00,325
It seems we're all here.
Then let's begin our meeting.

350
00:20:01,326 --> 00:20:04,037
For the further advancement
of the Yotsuba Group...

351
00:20:04,371 --> 00:20:06,873
and for our company to become
the greatest corporation in the world...

352
00:20:07,791 --> 00:20:09,209
Who shall we kill?

353
00:20:10,585 --> 00:20:13,380
It's tough to kill someone
every week...

354
00:20:14,047 --> 00:20:16,675
This may be irrelevant,

355
00:20:16,925 --> 00:20:19,761
but why has Kira
started killing like this?

356
00:20:20,220 --> 00:20:23,098
Takahashi,
haven't you figured it out?

357
00:20:24,766 --> 00:20:27,853
This is the most advantageous
course of action for Kira.

358
00:20:28,311 --> 00:20:30,647
Advantageous? The fact that
Kira has begun a killing service...

359
00:20:30,731 --> 00:20:32,107
is advantageous, Higuchi?

360
00:20:32,607 --> 00:20:35,318
I think you should keep quiet.

361
00:20:35,569 --> 00:20:37,404
You might be killed
for being such an idiot.

362
00:20:38,864 --> 00:20:41,575
The eight of us here are still young,

363
00:20:41,867 --> 00:20:45,078
but all of us have a chance of
landing in the CEO's chair before long.

364
00:20:45,662 --> 00:20:48,790
And since we started these meetings,

365
00:20:48,874 --> 00:20:51,418
our salaries have been raised well
above the other employees.

366
00:20:52,502 --> 00:20:55,756
It's kind of odd that Kira
would back a single company.

367
00:20:56,214 --> 00:20:57,382
No matter how I think about it...

368
00:20:58,091 --> 00:21:01,803
one of us here has to be Kira.

369
00:21:03,263 --> 00:21:08,769
TAKESHI OOI EIICHI TAKAHASHI
MASAHIKO KIDA KYOSUKE HIGUCHI

370
00:21:08,769 --> 00:21:10,270
So, back to business.
Does anyone have a proposal?

371
00:21:10,270 --> 00:21:14,357
TAKESHI OOI EIICHI TAKAHASHI
MASAHIKO KIDA KYOSUKE HIGUCHI

372
00:21:15,984 --> 00:21:17,486
Humans...

373
00:21:20,071 --> 00:21:21,823
are disgusting creatures...

374
00:21:22,115 --> 00:21:26,161
TO BE CONTINUED

375
00:21:26,620 --> 00:21:31,583
<i>I dreamed a dream
that no one could see,</i>

376
00:21:31,666 --> 00:21:36,963
<i>I threw away everything
that I didn't need</i>

377
00:21:37,214 --> 00:21:40,467
<i>I'm holding these feelings</i>

378
00:21:40,550 --> 00:21:45,972
<i>That I can't give up in my heart</i>

379
00:21:46,097 --> 00:21:52,354
<i>Even if my feet fall victim
to the shackles of sacrifice</i>

380
00:21:52,437 --> 00:21:56,942
<i>In between reality and my ideal</i>

381
00:21:57,734 --> 00:22:02,614
<i>I can't hold back
the flooding impulses</i>

382
00:22:02,906 --> 00:22:06,409
<i>Because I have a strong desire</i>

383
00:22:06,493 --> 00:22:10,080
<i>To accomplish</i>

384
00:22:10,705 --> 00:22:15,293
<i>[deceit] [fear] [vanity] [melancholy]</i>

385
00:22:15,585 --> 00:22:20,966
<i>I'm not weak enough to believe</i>

386
00:22:21,049 --> 00:22:26,054
<i>Any of these negative perceptions</i>

387
00:22:26,513 --> 00:22:31,852
<i>I'm a trickster
who doesn't know solitude</i>

388
00:22:36,147 --> 00:22:37,941
PREVIEW

389
00:22:38,316 --> 00:22:39,401
This is not good.

390
00:22:40,151 --> 00:22:44,990
The way you talk, it's almost like
you won't be satisfied unless I'm Kira...

391
00:22:45,740 --> 00:22:47,325
Stop messing around, Ryuzaki!

392
00:22:48,451 --> 00:22:51,162
NEXT EPISODE: ALLY

